.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-BANDWIDTH" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-bandwidth \- estimate total routing bandwidth
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-bandwidth
.SH DESCRIPTION
Computes the sum of
.B min(local_msat, remote_msat)
across all
.B CHANNELD_NORMAL
channels.
This is a rough upper bound on how much value the node can route in either direction simultaneously.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"bandwidth_msat":N, "channels":N}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-channel-summary (1),
.BR lightning-liquidity-report (1)
